## 3. Feature Requirements

### 3.1 Module 1: Tenant & User Management

**Priority:** P0 (Critical - MVP Blocker)  
**Target:** Month 1

#### Features:

**F1.1 Multi-Tenant Architecture**

- Each customer organization has isolated data (tenant)
- Subdomain-based access (e.g., `acme.supplex.com`)
- Tenant customization support (settings stored in JSONB)

**F1.2 User Authentication**

- Email/password login
- Password reset via email
- Session management (JWT tokens with tenant_id claim)
- Remember me functionality
- Password requirements: min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number

**F1.3 User Management**

- Add/edit/delete users within tenant
- User roles: Admin, Procurement, Quality, Viewer
- Role-based permissions enforcement
- User invitation via email
- User deactivation (soft delete)

**F1.4 Tenant Settings**

- Company information (name, address, logo)
- Email notification preferences
- Timezone selection
- Currency selection

---

### 3.2 Module 2: Supplier Master Data Management

**Priority:** P0 (Critical - MVP Blocker)  
**Target:** Month 1-2

#### Features:

**F2.1 Supplier CRUD Operations**

- Create new supplier profiles
- View supplier details
- Edit supplier information
- Delete suppliers (soft delete if has history)
- Supplier list with search and filters

**F2.2 Supplier Information Fields**

**Basic Information:**

- Supplier code (auto-generated or manual)
- Supplier name (required)
- Status: Prospect, Qualified, Approved, Blocked
- Registration date

**Contact Information:**

- Primary contact name, email, phone
- Secondary contacts (multiple)
- Website URL
- Physical address(es)

**Business Information:**

- Tax ID / VAT number
- Industry/sector
- Employee count range
- Annual revenue range (optional)

**Categorization:**

- Supplier category (dropdown, configurable)
- Product/service types
- Risk level: Low, Medium, High, Critical
- Supplier tier: Strategic, Preferred, Approved, Conditional

**Certifications:**

- Certification name (e.g., ISO 9001, IATF 16949)
- Certificate number
- Issue date / Expiry date
- Document upload

**Financial Information:**

- Payment terms
- Currency
- Credit limit (optional)
- Bank information (optional)

**F2.3 Document Management**

- Upload documents per supplier (PDF, images, Excel, Word)
- Document types: Certificate, Contract, Insurance, W9, Other
- Document expiry tracking
- Document version history
- Download documents
- Max file size: 25MB per file

**F2.4 Supplier Categorization**

- Manage supplier categories (hierarchy supported)
- Assign suppliers to categories
- Filter suppliers by category

**F2.5 Search & Filtering**

- Full-text search across supplier name, code, contacts
- Filter by status, category, risk level, certification expiry
- Sort by name, date added, risk level
- Pagination (25/50/100 per page)

---

### 3.3 Module 3: Supplier Qualification Workflow

**Priority:** P0 (Critical - MVP Blocker)  
**Target:** Month 2

#### Features:

**F3.1 Qualification Process Initiation**

- Start qualification for new or existing supplier
- Link to supplier profile
- Select qualification template (default for MVP)
- Assign requestor

**F3.2 Three-Stage Approval Workflow**

**Stage 1: Requestor/Initiator**

- Fill out qualification questionnaire
- Upload required documents
- Calculate initial risk score
- Submit for procurement review

**Stage 2: Procurement Review**

- Review submitted information
- Request additional information (send back to requestor)
- Add procurement notes
- Approve or reject for quality review

**Stage 3: Quality/Management Approval**

- Final review of qualification
- Add final notes
- Approve (supplier becomes "Qualified") or Reject
- If rejected, supplier status becomes "Blocked"

**F3.3 Qualification Questionnaire (MVP)**

- Basic template with 15-20 questions
- Question types: Yes/No, Rating (1-5), Text, File upload
- Questions organized by sections:
  - Quality Management System
  - Production Capabilities
  - Financial Stability
  - References
  - Compliance & Certifications

**F3.4 Risk Scoring**

- Automatic risk score calculation (0-100)
- Based on questionnaire answers
- Display as: Low (0-30), Medium (31-60), High (61-85), Critical (86-100)
- Configurable scoring weights per question (Phase 2)

**F3.5 Document Collection**

- Required documents checklist
- Mark documents as received/pending
- Upload documents directly to qualification
- Documents automatically linked to supplier profile

**F3.6 Email Notifications**

- Notify approver when ready for their review
- Notify requestor when sent back for changes
- Notify all stakeholders on final approval/rejection
- Reminder emails for pending approvals (after 3 days)

**F3.7 Qualification History**

- View all qualification attempts per supplier
- Audit trail of all actions (who, when, what)
- Comments/notes thread per qualification

---

### 3.4 Module 4: Performance Evaluation

**Priority:** P0 (Critical - MVP Blocker)  
**Target:** Month 2

#### Features:

**F4.1 Evaluation Creation**

- Create evaluation for approved suppliers
- Set evaluation period (start/end dates)
- Select evaluation template (default for MVP)
- Assign evaluator

**F4.2 Four Evaluation Dimensions**

**1. Quality (Weight: 30%)**

- Defect rate (%)
- Number of complaints in period
- CAPA response time
- Certificate compliance (up-to-date?)
- Manual rating (1-5)

**2. Delivery (Weight: 30%)**

- On-time delivery rate (%)
- Lead time accuracy
- Order completeness
- Manual rating (1-5)

**3. Service (Weight: 20%)**

- Responsiveness
- Communication quality
- Issue resolution
- Technical support
- Manual rating (1-5)

**4. Cost (Weight: 20%)**

- Price competitiveness
- Payment terms adherence
- Cost stability
- Manual rating (1-5)

**F4.3 Scoring System**

- Each dimension scored 1-5
- Overall score = weighted average
- Score interpretation:
  - Excellent: 4.5-5.0
  - Good: 3.5-4.49
  - Acceptable: 2.5-3.49
  - Poor: 1.5-2.49
  - Unacceptable: < 1.5

**F4.4 Manual Data Entry (MVP)**

- Evaluator manually enters metrics
- Auto-population from complaints data (Phase 2)
- Auto-population from ERP data (Phase 2)

**F4.5 Evaluation Workflow**

- Draft → In Progress → Completed
- Save as draft
- Submit for review (optional approval)
- Finalize evaluation (locks data)

**F4.6 Historical Trending**

- View past evaluations for supplier
- Trend charts showing dimension scores over time
- Compare current vs. previous period

**F4.7 Performance Alerts**

- Alert if overall score drops below 2.5 (poor)
- Alert if any dimension score < 2.0
- Email notifications to Admin and Quality roles

**F4.8 Evaluation Scheduling**

- Set evaluation frequency per supplier (monthly, quarterly, annual)
- Calendar view of upcoming evaluations
- Reminder notifications 1 week before due

---

### 3.5 Module 5: Complaint Tracking & CAPA

**Priority:** P0 (Critical - MVP Blocker)  
**Target:** Month 2

#### Features:

**F5.1 Complaint Registration**

- Create new complaint against supplier
- Auto-generated complaint number (format: CPL-YYYY-0001)
- Link to supplier
- Link to affected PO/part number (optional)

**F5.2 Complaint Information Fields**

**Basic Details:**

- Complaint number (auto)
- Date reported
- Reported by (user)
- Supplier
- Complaint category (dropdown)
- Severity: Low, Medium, High, Critical

**Description:**

- Problem description (rich text)
- Part/product affected
- Quantity affected
- Date discovered
- Immediate containment actions

**Classification:**

- Complaint type: Quality, Delivery, Service, Other
- Impact: Customer, Production, Inventory, None
- Financial impact (optional amount)

**F5.3 Complaint Categories (Configurable)**
Default categories:

- Defective material/parts
- Wrong quantity delivered
- Late delivery
- Missing documentation
- Packaging issues
- Non-conforming material
- Communication issues

**F5.4 Complaint Status Workflow**

- Open → Investigating → Awaiting Supplier → Resolved → Closed
- Status change triggers notifications
- Required fields per status:
  - Investigating: Root cause analysis required
  - Resolved: Corrective actions documented
  - Closed: Verification complete

**F5.5 Assignment & Tracking**

- Assign complaint to internal user (Quality Engineer)
- Due date calculation based on severity:
  - Critical: 24 hours
  - High: 3 days
  - Medium: 7 days
  - Low: 14 days
- SLA tracking (overdue indicator)
- Reassign capability

**F5.6 Root Cause Analysis**

- Root cause description (text area)
- Root cause method: 5 Why, Fishbone, Other (Phase 2: templates)
- Root cause determination date

**F5.7 CAPA (Corrective & Preventive Actions)**

- Add multiple corrective actions
- Each action has:
  - Description
  - Responsible party (internal or supplier)
  - Due date
  - Status: Pending, In Progress, Complete
  - Completion date
  - Verification notes

**F5.8 Document Attachments**

- Upload photos of defects
- Attach inspection reports
- Supplier response documents
- Evidence of corrective actions
- Max 10 files per complaint

**F5.9 Supplier Communication**

- Internal notes (visible to internal team only)
- External notes (shared with supplier - Phase 2: supplier portal)
- Email notification to supplier contact when complaint created
- Manual email capability

**F5.10 Complaint Resolution**

- Verify corrective actions completed
- Mark as resolved
- Closure notes
- Effectiveness rating (1-5)

**F5.11 Complaint Analytics**

- Complaints by supplier (count, by status)
- Complaints by category (Pareto chart)
- Average resolution time
- Recurring complaints (same supplier + same category)
- Financial impact summary

