### 4.3 Qualification Workflow

#### **US-3.1: Start Supplier Qualification**

**As a** Procurement user  
**I want to** initiate a qualification process for a new supplier  
**So that** I can ensure they meet our requirements

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] From supplier detail page, "Start Qualification" button
- [ ] Creates new qualification linked to supplier
- [ ] Qualification number auto-generated: QUAL-YYYY-0001
- [ ] Opens qualification form (Stage 1)
- [ ] Requestor field pre-filled with current user
- [ ] Status set to "Draft - Stage 1"
- [ ] Supplier cannot have multiple "In Progress" qualifications

**Priority:** P0  
**Estimate:** 3 story points

---

#### **US-3.2: Complete Qualification Questionnaire**

**As a** requestor  
**I want to** fill out the qualification questionnaire  
**So that** I can document the supplier's capabilities

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] Questionnaire divided into sections (Quality, Production, Financial, References, Compliance)
- [ ] Question types: Yes/No (radio), Rating 1-5 (stars), Text (textarea), File upload
- [ ] Progress indicator shows % complete
- [ ] Save as draft (can exit and return)
- [ ] Required questions marked with asterisk
- [ ] Cannot submit without completing required questions
- [ ] Risk score auto-calculated and displayed
- [ ] Upload required documents checklist
- [ ] Submit button moves to Stage 2

**Priority:** P0  
**Estimate:** 8 story points

---

#### **US-3.3: Approve Qualification (Procurement)**

**As a** Procurement Manager  
**I want to** review and approve Stage 2 qualifications  
**So that** I can validate supplier readiness

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] Notification email received when qualification enters Stage 2
- [ ] Review all questionnaire answers (read-only)
- [ ] Review uploaded documents
- [ ] Add procurement notes (text area)
- [ ] Three action buttons: Approve, Request Changes, Reject
- [ ] "Request Changes" sends back to Stage 1 with notes
- [ ] "Approve" moves to Stage 3
- [ ] "Reject" sets qualification status to "Rejected"
- [ ] All actions create audit log entry
- [ ] Email notifications sent on action

**Priority:** P0  
**Estimate:** 5 story points

---

#### **US-3.4: Final Approval (Quality/Management)**

**As a** Quality Manager or Admin  
**I want to** give final approval to qualified suppliers  
**So that** they can be used for production

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] Notification email when qualification enters Stage 3
- [ ] Review all previous stages (read-only)
- [ ] Add final approval notes
- [ ] Two actions: Approve or Reject
- [ ] "Approve" changes supplier status to "Qualified"
- [ ] "Approve" sets qualification status to "Approved"
- [ ] "Approve" records qualification date on supplier
- [ ] "Reject" changes supplier status to "Blocked"
- [ ] Email notification to all stakeholders
- [ ] Qualification locked (no further edits)

**Priority:** P0  
**Estimate:** 5 story points

---

### 4.4 Performance Evaluation

#### **US-4.1: Create Quarterly Evaluation**

**As a** Procurement or Quality user  
**I want to** create a performance evaluation for a supplier  
**So that** I can track their performance over time

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] From supplier page, "Create Evaluation" button
- [ ] Evaluation number auto-generated: EVAL-YYYY-Q1-0001
- [ ] Select evaluation period (start/end dates)
- [ ] Default to current quarter
- [ ] Cannot create overlapping evaluations for same supplier
- [ ] Assign evaluator (default: current user)
- [ ] Status set to "Draft"
- [ ] Opens evaluation form

**Priority:** P0  
**Estimate:** 5 story points

---

#### **US-4.2: Complete Evaluation Scoring**

**As an** evaluator  
**I want to** score a supplier across four dimensions  
**So that** I can document their performance

**Acceptance Criteria:**

- [ ] Four dimension sections: Quality, Delivery, Service, Cost
- [ ] Each dimension has:
  - Manual rating (1-5 stars, required)
  - Comments (textarea)
  - Supporting metrics (optional text fields for rates/percentages)
- [ ] Overall score auto-calculated: (Quality*0.3 + Delivery*0.3 + Service*0.2 + Cost*0.2)
- [ ] Overall score displayed prominently with color coding:
  - Green: 4.5-5.0 (Excellent)
  - Light green: 3.5-4.49 (Good)
  - Yellow: 2.5-3.49 (Acceptable)
  - Orange: 1.5-2.49 (Poor)
  - Red: < 1.5 (Unacceptable)
- [ ] Save as draft capability
- [ ] Finalize button (locks evaluation)
- [ ] Cannot edit after finalized

**Priority:** P0  
**Estimate:** 8 story points

---

