## 5. User Flows

### 5.1 User Flow: New Supplier Qualification

```
[Start] Procurement needs to qualify new supplier

1. Navigate to Suppliers
2. Click "Add New Supplier"
3. Fill basic information form
   - Required: Name, Status (Prospect)
4. Save supplier → Supplier created

5. From supplier detail page, click "Start Qualification"
6. Fill Stage 1 questionnaire
   - Answer 15-20 questions
   - Upload required documents
   - View calculated risk score
7. Save as draft (optional) OR Submit for review

8. Procurement Manager receives notification
9. Reviews Stage 1 submission
10. Decision point:
    - Request Changes → Back to step 6
    - Reject → Qualification ends, supplier blocked
    - Approve → Continue to step 11

11. Quality Manager receives notification
12. Reviews complete qualification
13. Decision point:
    - Reject → Supplier status = Blocked
    - Approve → Supplier status = Qualified

14. All stakeholders notified of final decision
15. Supplier now available for orders

[End]
```

**Happy Path Duration:** ~30 minutes (user time), 3-5 days (approval cycle)

---

### 5.2 User Flow: Register & Resolve Complaint

```
[Start] Quality Engineer discovers supplier defect

1. Navigate to Complaints
2. Click "Register New Complaint"
3. Fill complaint form:
   - Select supplier
   - Select category (Defective material)
   - Set severity (High)
   - Describe problem
   - Upload defect photos
4. Assign to self
5. Submit → Complaint created (Status: Open)

6. Email notification sent to assigned user and supplier

7. Quality Engineer investigates
8. Document root cause (Status changes to Investigating)
9. Determine 5 Why analysis results
10. Save root cause

11. Create corrective actions:
    - CAPA 1: Supplier to rework process (Due: 7 days)
    - CAPA 2: Supplier to provide updated procedure (Due: 14 days)
12. Change status to "Awaiting Supplier"

13. Supplier completes actions (tracked via email/phone)
14. Quality Engineer marks CAPAs as complete

15. Verify actions effective
16. Change status to "Resolved"
17. Add closure notes
18. Rate effectiveness: 4/5
19. Close complaint

20. Email notification sent to all parties

[End]
```

**Typical Duration:** 7-14 days from registration to closure

---

### 5.3 User Flow: Quarterly Evaluation

```
[Start] It's end of quarter, time to evaluate suppliers

1. Navigate to Suppliers
2. Filter by Status = Approved
3. For each supplier:

   4. Click supplier name → Detail page
   5. Click "Create Evaluation"
   6. Set evaluation period (auto-populated with current quarter)
   7. Confirm → Evaluation created

   8. Open evaluation form
   9. Score Quality dimension:
      - Enter defect rate: 2.3%
      - Review complaints: 1 open
      - Rate overall quality: 4/5
      - Add comments

   10. Score Delivery dimension:
      - Enter on-time delivery: 95%
      - Rate overall: 5/5

   11. Score Service dimension:
      - Rate responsiveness: 4/5

   12. Score Cost dimension:
      - Rate price competitiveness: 3/5

   13. Review overall score: 4.0 (Good)
   14. Save as draft OR Finalize

   15. If finalized → Evaluation locked
   16. If overall score < 2.5 → Alert sent to management

17. Repeat for all suppliers

18. Review dashboard to see updated scores

[End]
```

**Time per Evaluation:** 10-15 minutes  
**Frequency:** Quarterly

