## 6. Functional Requirements

### 6.1 Authentication & Authorization

**FR-1.1: Multi-Factor Authentication**

- OUT OF SCOPE for MVP (Phase 2)

**FR-1.2: Session Management**

- JWT tokens expire after 8 hours of inactivity
- Refresh token mechanism for seamless session extension
- "Remember me" extends session to 30 days
- User can be logged in on max 3 devices simultaneously

**FR-1.3: Role-Based Access Control**

| Feature                          | Admin | Procurement | Quality | Viewer |
| -------------------------------- | ----- | ----------- | ------- | ------ |
| Manage users                     | ✅    | ❌          | ❌      | ❌     |
| Manage settings                  | ✅    | ❌          | ❌      | ❌     |
| Create suppliers                 | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ❌     |
| Edit suppliers                   | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ❌     |
| Delete suppliers                 | ✅    | ✅          | ❌      | ❌     |
| Start qualifications             | ✅    | ✅          | ❌      | ❌     |
| Approve qualifications (Stage 2) | ✅    | ✅          | ❌      | ❌     |
| Approve qualifications (Stage 3) | ✅    | ❌          | ✅      | ❌     |
| Create evaluations               | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ❌     |
| Finalize evaluations             | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ❌     |
| Create complaints                | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ❌     |
| Close complaints                 | ✅    | ❌          | ✅      | ❌     |
| View dashboards                  | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ✅     |
| Export data                      | ✅    | ✅          | ✅      | ❌     |

**FR-1.4: Audit Logging**

- All create/update/delete operations logged
- Log includes: User, Action, Timestamp, Entity Type, Entity ID, Changes (before/after)
- Logs retained for 7 years
- Logs accessible to Admin role only

---

### 6.2 Data Management

**FR-2.1: Soft Delete**

- Suppliers, evaluations, complaints use soft delete
- Deleted items hidden from UI but retained in database
- Admin can view deleted items and restore if needed

**FR-2.2: Data Validation**

- Email addresses validated using regex
- Phone numbers accept international formats
- URLs validated as proper format
- File uploads validated for type and size
- SQL injection prevented via parameterized queries
- XSS prevention via input sanitization

**FR-2.3: Data Retention**

- Active data: Indefinite retention
- Soft-deleted data: 90 days, then hard delete
- Audit logs: 7 years
- Uploaded files: Deleted when parent entity hard deleted

---

### 6.3 Notification System

**FR-3.1: Email Notifications**

- Triggered by: User invited, Qualification stage change, Evaluation created, Complaint assigned, CAPA due soon (1 day before), Password reset, Password changed
- Email template branded with tenant logo
- Unsubscribe link in footer (user preference)
- Sent via AWS SES or SendGrid

**FR-3.2: In-App Notifications (Phase 2)**

- OUT OF SCOPE for MVP

**FR-3.3: Notification Preferences**

- User can enable/disable each notification type
- Default: All enabled except marketing

---

### 6.4 Search & Filtering

**FR-4.1: Full-Text Search**

- Search uses PostgreSQL full-text search (MVP)
- Searches across: Supplier name, code, contact names, contact emails
- Case-insensitive
- Results ranked by relevance
- Debounced 300ms to reduce queries

**FR-4.2: Advanced Filtering**

- Multiple filters combine with AND logic
- Filter options persist in URL query params (shareable links)
- Applied filters shown as removable tags
- Filter state saved per user (Phase 2)

---

### 6.5 File Management

**FR-5.1: File Upload**

- Max file size: 25MB per file
- Accepted types: PDF, DOC, DOCX, XLS, XLSX, JPG, PNG, GIF
- Virus scanning via ClamAV (Phase 2) or Supabase Edge Function
- Files stored in Supabase Storage with tenant path prefix
- File access controlled via RLS policies

**FR-5.2: File Download**

- Pre-signed URLs generated for secure download
- URLs expire after 1 hour
- Download tracked in audit log

---

## 7. Non-Functional Requirements

### 7.1 Performance

**NFR-1.1: Page Load Time**

- 90% of pages load in < 2 seconds on 3G connection
- 95% of pages load in < 1 second on 4G connection
- Dashboard loads in < 2 seconds with 1000 suppliers

**NFR-1.2: API Response Time**

- 95% of API requests respond in < 500ms
- 99% of API requests respond in < 1000ms
- Bulk operations (exports) can take up to 30 seconds

**NFR-1.3: Database Performance**

- All queries optimized with proper indexes
- N+1 query problems eliminated via eager loading
- Database connection pooling (max 20 connections per tenant)

**NFR-1.4: Scalability**

- System supports up to 50 tenants in MVP
- Each tenant supports up to 500 suppliers
- Each tenant supports up to 50 users
- System scales horizontally via Vercel serverless functions

---

### 7.2 Security

**NFR-2.1: Data Encryption**

- All data encrypted at rest (AES-256) via Supabase
- All data encrypted in transit (TLS 1.3)
- Passwords hashed using bcrypt (salt rounds: 12)
- Sensitive fields (API keys) encrypted at application level

**NFR-2.2: Multi-Tenancy Isolation**

- Row-Level Security (RLS) policies enforce tenant isolation
- All queries filtered by tenant_id automatically
- JWT tokens include tenant_id claim
- No cross-tenant data leakage possible

**NFR-2.3: Authentication Security**

- Password requirements: Min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number, 1 special char
- Account lockout after 5 failed login attempts (15 min cooldown)
- Password reset tokens expire after 1 hour
- JWT tokens include expiration claim

**NFR-2.4: API Security**

- Rate limiting: 1000 requests/hour per tenant
- API authentication via JWT or API key
- CORS configured for specific domains only
- SQL injection prevention via parameterized queries
- XSS prevention via input sanitization and Content Security Policy headers

**NFR-2.5: Compliance**

- GDPR compliant (data export, right to erasure)
- SOC 2 Type II preparation (audit trail, access controls)
- CCPA compliant

---

### 7.3 Availability

**NFR-3.1: Uptime**

- Target: 99.5% uptime (MVP)
- Goal: 99.9% uptime (Production)
- Planned maintenance windows: Sunday 2-4 AM UTC

**NFR-3.2: Disaster Recovery**

- Database backups: Daily automated via Supabase
- Point-in-time recovery available
- RTO (Recovery Time Objective): 2 hours
- RPO (Recovery Point Objective): 24 hours (daily backups)

**NFR-3.3: Monitoring**

- Uptime monitoring via Vercel Analytics
- Error tracking via Sentry
- Performance monitoring via Vercel Insights
- Database monitoring via Supabase Dashboard
- Alerts for: Downtime, Error rate > 1%, API response time > 1s

---

### 7.4 Usability

**NFR-4.1: Browser Support**

- Chrome 90+ (primary)
- Firefox 88+
- Safari 14+
- Edge 90+
- No IE 11 support

**NFR-4.2: Responsive Design**

- Desktop-first design (primary use case)
- Tablet support (iPad landscape)
- Mobile support (limited to dashboards and viewing)
- Mobile-optimized forms (Phase 2)

**NFR-4.3: Accessibility**

- WCAG 2.1 Level A compliance (minimum)
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader friendly
- Color contrast ratios meet AA standards
- Alt text on images

**NFR-4.4: Internationalization**

- OUT OF SCOPE for MVP (English only)
- Phase 2: Multi-language support (Spanish, French, German)

---

### 7.5 Maintainability

**NFR-5.1: Code Quality**

- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- ESLint configured with recommended rules
- Prettier for code formatting
- Code coverage target: 70% (unit + integration tests)
- No critical or high severity vulnerabilities in dependencies

**NFR-5.2: Documentation**

- API documentation via OpenAPI/Swagger
- User guide with screenshots
- Developer setup guide in README
- Architecture decision records (ADRs)

**NFR-5.3: Deployment**

- Automated deployment via GitHub Actions
- Zero-downtime deployments
- Rollback capability within 5 minutes
- Preview deployments for each PR

