## 10. UI/UX Requirements

### 10.1 Design System

**UI Framework:** shadcn/ui components with Tailwind CSS

**Color Palette:**

- Primary: Blue (#3B82F6)
- Success: Green (#10B981)
- Warning: Yellow (#F59E0B)
- Error: Red (#EF4444)
- Neutral: Gray scale (#F9FAFB to #111827)

**Typography:**

- Font family: Inter (sans-serif)
- Headings: 600 weight
- Body: 400 weight
- Small text: 14px
- Body text: 16px
- H1: 32px
- H2: 24px
- H3: 20px

**Spacing:**

- Use Tailwind's spacing scale (4px base unit)
- Card padding: 24px
- Section margins: 32px

### 10.2 Layout

**Navigation:**

- Top navigation bar (sticky)
  - Logo (left)
  - Main navigation (center): Suppliers, Qualifications, Evaluations, Complaints, Dashboard
  - User menu (right): Profile, Settings, Logout
- Breadcrumb navigation below top nav
- No sidebar for MVP (future consideration)

**Page Layout:**

- Max content width: 1400px
- Centered on large screens
- Responsive breakpoints: 640px (sm), 768px (md), 1024px (lg), 1280px (xl)

### 10.3 Components

**Tables:**

- Striped rows
- Hover state
- Sortable column headers (click to sort)
- Pagination controls at bottom
- Loading skeleton during data fetch
- Empty state with helpful message and CTA

**Forms:**

- Labels above fields
- Required fields marked with red asterisk
- Inline validation on blur
- Error messages below fields in red
- Success state after submission
- Disabled state for readonly forms

**Buttons:**

- Primary: Filled blue
- Secondary: Outlined blue
- Danger: Filled red
- Text: Underline on hover
- Sizes: Small (32px), Medium (40px), Large (48px)
- Icons supported (left or right)

**Cards:**

- White background
- 1px border (#E5E7EB)
- 8px border radius
- Box shadow on hover (subtle)

**Modals:**

- Overlay with 50% opacity black background
- Centered modal
- Close button (X) top right
- Max width: 600px
- Accessible (focus trap, ESC to close)

**Toasts:**

- Position: Top right
- Auto-dismiss after 5 seconds
- Types: Success (green), Error (red), Info (blue), Warning (yellow)
- Can be manually dismissed

### 10.4 Page-Specific Requirements

#### Supplier List Page

- Search bar prominent at top
- Filters in collapsible panel on left (or top on mobile)
- Table with columns: Code, Name, Status, Category, Risk Level, Score, Open Complaints, Actions
- Status badge (color-coded)
- Risk level badge (color-coded)
- Actions dropdown: View, Edit, Evaluate, Report Complaint, Delete
- Add New Supplier button (primary, top right)

#### Supplier Detail Page

- Header with supplier name and status badge
- Tabs: Overview, Performance, Complaints, Documents, History
- Overview tab: All supplier information in sections
- Edit button (top right)
- Quick actions: Evaluate, Report Complaint, Start Qualification

#### Dashboard Page

- Grid layout (responsive)
- KPI cards: 4 across on desktop, 2 on tablet, 1 on mobile
- Charts: Use Chart.js or Recharts
- Interactive charts (hover for details)
- Date range picker prominent
- Refresh button to reload data

#### Qualification Workflow Page

- Wizard-style interface (if creating new)
- Progress indicator: Stage 1 → Stage 2 → Stage 3
- Section-based questionnaire
- Progress percentage bar
- Save Draft button (secondary)
- Submit button (primary)
- Previous responses shown when reviewing

#### Evaluation Form

- Four dimension sections (collapsible cards)
- Star rating component (1-5)
- Text inputs for metrics (defect rate, on-time %)
- Overall score displayed prominently at top (updates live)
- Color-coded score: Green (>4.5), Yellow (2.5-4.5), Red (<2.5)
- Save Draft and Finalize buttons

#### Complaint Form

- Single-page form (not wizard)
- Severity selector prominent (radio buttons with colors)
- Rich text editor for description (basic formatting)
- File upload with drag-and-drop
- Due date auto-calculated and displayed
- Preview uploaded files

